</p>
<p class="title">[[1209/06:39]</p>
<p class="para">The bottom floor was even more frigid than the elevator hall, and smelled of rust and dust. While it wasn't pitch-dark, the dim light required them to watch their feet when they walked.
</p><p class="para">"What's that?"
</p><p class="para">Rose, who was leading the group, stopped. No. 2 strained her eyes to see what Rose was pointing at.
</p><p class="para">"Humans?"
</p><p class="para">Rose cautiously moved closer. As they approached the figures, it became clear from their silhouettes that they were indeed at least humanoid. They were small, and were wearing wide-hemmed clothing. 
</p><p class="para">"Red clothes? Girls?"
</p><p class="para">Two girls wearing identical outfits—a short one-piece in a vivid red that was visible in the darkness.
</p><p class="para">No. 4 spoke in an unusually deep voice. "Those red girls... they don't look like your average children."
</p><p class="para">At the very least, they weren't human. Their heat signatures didn't match those of humans, and there weren't any humans left on Earth in the first place.
</p><p class="para">"<i>Welcome.</i>"
